for me the cutover point (for copy&paste or overloads or...) is usually three. i have no reasonable basis for that, but it at least makes me somewhat consistent :-)

i feel like it fits https://google.github.io/styleguide/cppguide.html#Default_Arguments too.

i guess also "most people don't need either of two extra arguments, more people will need the first of them than the second"... it's really ticking the "there's a big difference between the `argv` argument and the other arguments, and overloading makes that less clear" box.

